							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/bpietras/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/Pietras-headshot-1-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/Pietras-headshot-1-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="B. Pietras" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/bpietras/">B. Pietras</a></h6>
										B. Pietras is a writer with essays in <em>Creative Nonfiction, TriQuarterly, Electric Literature</em>, and elsewhere. They are currently at work on a book about what the last five hundred years of queer history can teach us about living a meaningful life. You can find him online at bpietras.com and on Twitter @reliqueery.																			</div>
