				<div id="post_more_wrapper" class="hiding">
			<a href="javascript:;" id="post_more_close"><i class="fa fa-times-circle"></i></a>
			<div class="more_story_title">Read More</div>
			<div class="inner">
						<div class="post_more_img_wrapper">
				<a href="https://lithub.com/tyranny-as-tragedy-on-king-lear-maoist-china-and-the-unpredictable-nature-of-power/">
					<img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/cultural-revolution-300x300.jpg" alt=""/>
				</a>
			</div>
						<a class="post_more_title" href="https://lithub.com/tyranny-as-tragedy-on-king-lear-maoist-china-and-the-unpredictable-nature-of-power/">
				<h4 style="margin:0">Tyranny as Tragedy: On <em>King Lear</em>, Maoist China and the Unpredictable Nature of Power</h4>
			</a>
			I had a remarkable freshman student who intuitively understood the modality of totalitarianism, and how it might be represented...			
